The paper deals with maintaining a maximal independent set in a fully dynamic graph, which involves data structures and algorithms for dynamic graphs (cs.DS). The algorithm presented in the paper has an amortized update time that depends on the maximum degree of the graph, which suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.Distributed) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions a distributed implementation of the algorithm, which further supports the relevance to distributed computing. Finally, the paper presents a sublinear update time algorithm, which is a common topic in the subfield of sublinear algorithms (cs.SI).
